              simulation",
  author   = "Wirth, Oliver and Slaven, James and Taylor, Matthew A",
  abstract = "A simulation study was conducted to provide a more thorough
              account of measurement error associated with interval sampling
              methods. A computer program simulated the application of
              momentary time sampling, partial-interval recording, and
              whole-interval recording methods on target events randomly
              distributed across an observation period. The simulation yielded
              measures of error for multiple combinations of observation
