  author   = "Powell, J and Martindale, B and Kulp, S and Martindale, A and
              Bauman, R",
  abstract = "A person manufactured his in-seat behavior for 15, 30-min
              sessions so that there were three blocks of five sessions where
              the behavior occurred 20\%, 50\%, and 80\% of the time. Whole
              interval, partial interval, and momentary time-sample measures of
              the behavior were taken and compared to the continuous measure of
              the behavior i.e., per cent of time the behavior occurred. For
              interval time sampling, the difference between the continuous and
              sample measures i.e., measurement error, was: (1) extensive, (2)
              unidirectional, (3) a function of the time per response, and (4)
