              of behavior are confounded in interval time sampling. Momentary
              time sampling was found to be superior to interval time sampling
              in estimating the duration a behavior occurs.",
  journal  = "J. Appl. Behav. Anal.",
  volume   =  10,
  number   =  2,
  pages    = "325--332",
  year     =  1977,
  language = "en"
}

